{"tid":2366413,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"拜登既太空發展既顧問 建議同中國合作","createTime":"2021-01-14T12:54:57.000Z","updateTime":"2021-01-15T01:01:22.000Z","uid":48083,"like":18,"dislike":273,"uniUserReply":101,"replies":[{"pid":"76f033b00b516d6a33937519fc61ed6887a397fb","tid":2366413,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-14T12:54:57.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.politico.com/news/2020/12/20/biden-china-space-448529\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2020%2F12%2F20%2Fbiden-china-space-448529&d=qXcR1A%2FTALq%2FhnoNE0cJVSC3g8rst4cc2NZsp7q1N1o%3D&h=eb433a8f\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.politico.com/news/2020/12/20/biden-china-space-448529</a><br />\n<br />\n<br />\nTop advisers to Joe Biden have argued that it's important to cooperate with China on space exploration, even as the incoming administration treats Beijing as its top economic and military competitor in virtually every other realm.<br />\n<br />\nThey assert that despite China's pattern of stealing American technology and diverting it for military purposes, a limited space partnership between Washington and Beijing could reduce tensions and the likelihood of a destabilizing space race. The move would be akin to the cooperation between the U.S. and Russia's civilian space programs during the height of the Cold War.<br />\n<br />\nAdvertisement<br />\nThe debate gained more urgency recently after China became just the third nation to retrieve samples from the moon, the latest in a series of major achievements for its ambitious space program.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Trying to exclude them I think is a failing strategy,&rdquo; Pam Melroy, a former astronaut who is serving on Biden&rsquo;s NASA transition team and is among those being considered to lead the space agency, told POLITICO before the election. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s very important that we engage.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nMost of the nearly two dozen former astronauts, government officials and space experts interviewed by POLITICO agreed that America could lose its position as the global space leader if it shuts Beijing out entirely.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;My concern is not that China is going places, but that our partners are going to China,&rdquo; said former NASA administrator and astronaut Charles Bolden, who endorsed Biden and worked with him in the Obama administration. &ldquo;We seem to be satisfied to allow them to go off and build their own space station. &hellip; That&rsquo;s short sighted. &hellip; It&rsquo;s not the mark of a good leader.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nAdvertisement<br />\nThe transition team declined to comment on Biden's plans for China and space. Biden has said little about space during the campaign and has not broached the issue of working with China on exploration.<br />\n<br />\nA move toward peace through space would be difficult to reconcile with China's aggressive actions, including the theft of intellectual property, abuse of religious leaders and cultural minorities, and development of anti-satellite weapons."},{"pid":"c8bb97af56075febc47fa0759b74d63f392b5003","tid":2366413,"uid":70487,"like":47,"dislike":2,"score":45,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-01-14T12:56:17.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/cat/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />民主左派多行不義得罪主"},{"pid":"32ba9f396fb019ece8a988abc4ac0aa037ba1f17","tid":2366413,"uid":4783,"like":84,"dislike":4,"score":80,"citedBy":8,"replyTime":"2021-01-14T12:56:22.000Z","msg":"兩黨共識撚請回應下<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"070a89ad323daadd91cfbbdcb9b03edaffe6c537","tid":2366413,"uid":289708,"like":40,"dislike":1,"score":39,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-01-14T12:57:53.000Z","msg":"中國2025重新出發!"},{"pid":"f55d044255475ca5a8aa37a1c4d6764b32a42c40","tid":2366413,"uid":42586,"like":38,"dislike":0,"score":38,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-14T13:00:04.000Z","msg":"比少少碎銀收買啲顧問又可以痴美國科技<br />\n支那今次又贏"},{"pid":"90418210e5f50124b6c383f26b6cd121fdcf6ede","ti